Personalize Service Documents with Embedded Expressions

Integrate field values into rich text components to incorporate your companyâ€™s voice and style throughout your service documents. With embedded expressions, you can merge field values in rich text components to style the text, reference field values without field names, and improve the flow of your document.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

How: In Document Builder, drag a rich text component onto the canvas. Optionally, add static text to give context for the embedded field. To embed the field into the rich text component use the syntax: {!Record.fieldname} or {!Record.Objectname.fieldname}. For example, to embed a phone number for an account, the syntax is {!Record.Account.phone}. Save the template, and then test it on the document preview.
title: Personalize Service Documents with Embedded Expressions
